'''Komi De''' (Ԁ&nbsp;ԁ; italics: <span style="font-family: times, Times New Roman, serif; font-size: larger">''Ԁ&nbsp;ԁ''</span>) is a letter of the [[Molodtsov alphabet]], a version of [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic]]. It was used only in the writing of the [[Komi language]] in the 1920s and in the [[Mordvin language]].{{citation needed | date=April 2011 | reason=not shown anywhere in the Mordvin language articles}}  The lowercase form resembles the lowercase of the [[D|Latin letter D]] (d&nbsp;<span style="font-family: times, Times New Roman, serif; font-size: larger">''d''</span>) and its uppercase form resembles an upside-down capital [[P|Latin letter P]] or a reversed [[soft sign]]. 

Komi De represents the [[voiced dental plosive]] {{ipa|/d/}}, like the pronunciation of {{angbr|d}} in "'''d'''in". This sound is represented by the [[De (Cyrillic)|Cyrillic letter De]] (Д&nbsp;д) in other Cyrillic alphabets.

